@@ -206,6 +207,14 @@ Add `--no-quit` to `pnpm playtest:fixture` for interactive observation (keeps `-
 
 After the process exits, JSON lands at `user://harness_summaries/<UTC>.json` and burst captures at `user://frames/<session_tag>/burst-N-K.png`. Console output `ScriptedInput CLI: ...` lines confirm each flag was parsed. Unknown flags are silently ignored so adding new flags doesn't break existing invocations.
 
+### Runtime termination enforcement (ADR-025 A2, PR3)
+
+The fixture's declared **run-class** + **`max_ticks`** budget are enforced at runtime so an automated run can never hang (the `interior_breach_loop` hang that motivated A2):
+
+- **Class-B hard-refuse** — pointing the automated path (`--auto-start` / `--quit-on-end`, without `--manual`) at a `run_class == MANUAL` fixture **refuses loudly and exits non-zero (`2`) before the harness timer starts** (`push_error`, no world-build). A manual fixture has no bounded termination; warn-and-run was the silent-degrade A2 forbids. `--manual` is the explicit live/human opt-in.
+- **`max_ticks` budget** — `ScriptedInput` counts every harness tick; at `max_ticks` it force-terminates **before** the launcher's wall-clock watchdog SIGKILL (the graceful inner layer). A no-drive `TickBudget` fixture (`empty_grid_vehicle_east`) runs in **budget-only** mode — the counter is the entire run. Budget exhaustion writes a distinct **`fixture_timeout` envelope** (a top-level `status` key, distinct from the normal summary schema), not a 259 summary.
+- **Exit codes** — `0` clean drive-end **or** a planned `TickBudget` completion (`status: "budget_reached"`); `1` summary-write failure; `2` Class-B refused on the automated path; `3` `max_ticks` backstop tripped on a non-`TickBudget` fixture that failed to self-terminate (`status: "fixture_timeout"`); `124` the launcher watchdog SIGKILL (`run-godot.cjs`, the un-bypassable outer backstop).
+
 ## Known limitations (v1)
 
 - **Ghost slots in `slot_stuck_histogram`** — the sim's `BufferSlot` index recycling means a single `slot_index` row may aggregate stuck-tick counts from multiple unrelated agents over the run. Bit-stable across **identical-script** runs (the diff use case); across **different-script** runs the ghost-row count may vary. Spec §`slot_stuck_histogram` documents the FFI mechanic.
